Dan Nelson wrote:
> ${SHELL} may be not be a bourne shell.  Just stick a #!/bin/sh at the
> top of the script itself.

Configure sets SHELL explicitly during initialization.  The #! syntax
wasn't always portable --- chances are zsh doesn't even compile on
systems that old, but in this case using SHELL is the portable way
to do it.

